==English==
===Adjective===
'''extraordinaire'''

# [[extraordinary]] (suitable for use only in certain situations; see usage notes)
#: ''He was a dancer extraordinaire.''

====Usage notes====
* this adjective '''always''' appears '''after''' the noun
* this adjective is usually only used to describe people/animals which are good at their intended purpose. 
::For example:
:::She was a businesswoman extraordinaire.
::::::OR
:::That dancing elephant is an entertainer extraordinaire.
::But usually '''not''':
:::That is a game extraordinaire.
:Although the latter is not technically incorrect, to a native English speaker familiar with the word, it would normally sound incorrect.

